<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7626265>
    dc:description "FIGURE 34. A, B, Mecataleptodius parvulus (Fabricius, 1793), gen. nov., comb. nov., male, cl 6.5 mm, cw 10 mm (MZUSP" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7626265/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7626267>
    dc:description "FIGURE 35. A–E, First male gonopods. A–C, Cataleptodius floridanus (Gibbes, 1850). A, B, Male, cl 17 mm, cw 27 mm (MZUSP 9937). C, Male from Tortugas, Florida, cl 7 mm, cw 11 mm (after Monod 1956: 293, fig. 356, as Xantho floridana, reproduced by Guinot 1968: 707, fig. 23, as Cataleptodius floridanus). D, Mecataleptodius parvulus (Fabricius, 1793), gen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7626267/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7626271>
    dc:description "FIGURE 36. A–D, First male gonopods. A, Leptodius exaratus (H. Milne Edwards, 1834), type species of Leptodius A. Milne- Edwards, 1869, neotype, cl 16.1 mm, cw 23.7 mm, after Lee et al. (2013:195, fig. 4B). B, Xantho hydrophilus (Herbst, 1790), senior synonym of Cancer incisus Leach, 1814, type species of Xantho Leach, 1814, after Drach & Forest (1953:18, fig. 21, as Xantho floridus Montagu, 1808). C, Cataleptodius occidentalis (Stimpson, 1871), after Holthuis (1954: 30, fig. 11b). D, Xanthodius sternberghii Stimpson, 1859, type species of Xanthodius Stimpson, 1859 (after López 1990)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7626271/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

